    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Historical Information
</head>
      <p>Fairfax County was named for Thomas Fairfax, sixth baron Fairfax of Cameron, proprietor of the Northern Neck. It was formed from Prince William County in 1742. Its area is 410 square miles, and the county seat is Fairfax.
</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>Miscellaneous Fairfax County (Va.) Records, 1731-1857, consists of Court Records, Miscellaneous Court Papers, Petition of John Middleton, Rent Rolls, Road and Bridge Papers, Road Petitions, and Tithables. 
</p>
    </scopecontent>
